	<h1>
Montreal Regional Science Fair officially begins
</h1>
	<div class="page-title-hline">&nbsp;</div>
	










<!-- MAIN CONTENT AREA - START -->



		<div class="floatright">
			<br class="hide" />
<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="sidebar" --><!-- FCKEDITOR_sidebar --><!-- /FCKEDITOR_sidebar --> <!-- InstanceEndEditable -->

<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="Sidebar" --><!-- InstanceEndEditable --><br class="hide" />
			</div>


			<div class="contentcolumn">
				<br class="hide" />
<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="maincontent" --><!-- FCKEDITOR_maincontent --><!-- /FCKEDITOR_maincontent -->

	<div id="entry-117">
		<div class="entry-header">
			<!--<h2 class="asset-name entry-title">
Montreal Regional Science Fair officially begins
</h2>-->
			<div class="entry-meta" title="2010-03-21T15:36:20-05:00">Sunday Mar 21, 2010</div>
		</div>
	
		<div class="entry-content">
			<div class="entry-body">
				
The 2010<a href="http://www.exposciencesbell.qc.ca/en/100-index.htm"> Bell Montreal Regional Science &amp; Technology Fair</a> began today at Concordia University. Co-hosted by the Faculty of Engineering &amp; Computer Science and the Faculty of Arts &amp; Science, this edition of the MRSTF marks the 50th anniversary of science fairs in the province, as well as the first time the event has been hosted by a university.<br /><br /><img alt="Bell Montreal Regional Science & Technology Fair 2010" src="http://newsfeed.encs.concordia.ca/encs_test/expo1.jpg" class="mt-image-center" style="text-align: center; display: block; margin: 0pt auto 20px;" height="278" width="440" />At this afternoon's opening ceremonies, Concordia's <a href="http://provost.concordia.ca/">Provost</a>, <b>David Graham</b>, gave a warm welcome to the excited crowd of high school and CEGEP students, here representing their schools and exhibiting their winning science projects. At the Provost's mention of the 10 entrance scholarships available to be won, the crowd erupted in cheers and applause. <br /><br /><img alt="Bell Montreal Regional Science & Technology Fair 2010" src="http://newsfeed.encs.concordia.ca/encs_test/expo2.jpg" class="mt-image-center" style="text-align: center; display: block; margin: 0pt auto 20px;" height="204" width="440" />The Honourable <a href="http://www.marcgarneau.ca/"><b>Marc Garneau</b></a>, MP for Westmount and Ville-Marie, received a similarly warm reception. He shared inspiring insights with the assembled students, encouraging them to always be curious and speaking of how his training as an engineer helped him become the first Canadian in space. "Anybody who does science is on an adventure," he said. "You are going where no one has gone before."<br /><br /><img alt="Bell Montreal Regional Science & Technology Fair 2010" src="http://newsfeed.encs.concordia.ca/encs_test/expo3.jpg" class="mt-image-center" style="text-align: center; display: block; margin: 0pt auto 20px;" height="248" width="440" />After the opening ceremonies, ENCS's <a href="../administration-and-governance/about-the-dean/index.html">Dean Robin Drew</a> then welcomed invited guests to a special VIP reception in honour of the 2010 Bell Montreal Regional Science &amp; Technology Fair. Dean Drew said that he was sure that this fantastic event would inspire the scientific minds of tomorrow and also expressed hope that some of the bright young students here for the event would one day return to Concordia as part of the student body. <b>Agostino Porchetta</b>, President of the <b><a href="http://www.sciencetech.ca/">Educational Alliance for Science &amp; Technology</a></b> and <b>Wilson Wong</b>, Director of EAST were also on hand to say some words of welcome and to present Deans Drew and Lewis with commemorative posters from the event. <br /><br />For more on Exposcience, be sure to check out our <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/encs-concordia/sets/72157623540615113/">photos on Flickr</a>.<br /><div><br /></div>

			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	
	
	
